text: The men's 100 meter running deer, double shots was a shooting sports event held as part of the shooting at the 1912 Summer Olympics programme. It was the second appearance of the event, which had been introduced in 1908. The competition was held on Wednesday, 3 July 1912. Twenty sport shooters from six nations competed. ==Results== {| class=wikitable style="text-align:center" |- !
